Sass & Less Compilation Concepts
Theory Overview
Preprocessors like Sass (Syntactically Awesome Stylesheets) and Less expand standard CSS features with functional programming capabilities. They convert advanced precompiled syntax sheets into standard, production-ready browser CSS configurations.
•	Variables: Define global design constants once (e.g., $brand-primary: #4f46e5;) to update styling values across all files instantly.
•	Nesting: Nest your CSS rules to match the structural hierarchy of your HTML document, making stylesheets significantly cleaner and easier to read.
•	Mixins: Group sets of reusable CSS rules together into custom functions that accept style parameters on the fly:
// SCSS Structural Mixin Example
@mixin generate-flex-card($justify, $align) {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: $justify;
    align-items: $align;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

// Layout Use Instance.main-feature-box {
    @include generate-flex-card(center, space-between);
    background-color: var(--neutral-light);
}
